results.name: Multiplicative with a(p^e) = A005940(p^e).
comment: Question: are there any other numbers n besides 1 and those in A070776, for which a(n) = A005940(n)? At least not below 2^25. This is probably easy to prove.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..16384
Index entries for sequences related to binary expansion of n
example: For n = 85 = 5*17, a(85) = A005940(5) * A005940(17) = 5*11 = 55. Note that A005940(5) is obtained from the binary expansion of 5-1 = 4, which is "100", and A005940(17) is obtained from the binary expansion of 17-1 = 16, which is "1000".
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Feb 15 2019
